  "query": "What is the current level of crude oil in the US Strategic Petroleum Reserve as of June 2026, per EIA weekly data (WCSSTUS1)? What has been the weekly trajectory over the past 3-6 months (fills or releases)?",
  "answer": "Research complete. Summary of findings:\n\n**Current level (week ending June 26, 2026):** US SPR crude oil stocks were **325,655 thousand barrels (~325.66 million bbl)** per EIA series WCSSTUS1 \u2014 the lowest since May 1983, down ~19.1% year-over-year.\n\n**Weekly trajectory (past 3-6 months):** Two distinct phases:\n1. **Dec 2025 \u2013 late March 2026:** Slow fill/plateau, building from ~411.9M to a peak of ~415.4M barrels held flat through Feb/March.\n2. **Late March \u2013 June 2026:** Rapid, accelerating **drawdown** \u2014 ~89.8M barrels released from peak to June 26, running roughly 7\u201310M barrels/week (peaking at \u22129.9M in the week ending May 15), decelerating to \u22125.5M in the final week.\n\n**Driver:** A coordinated IEA emergency release of 400M barrels globally following Middle East/Iran conflict, with the US committing 172M barrels, structured as an exchange. All data sourced primarily from EIA's Weekly Petroleum Status Report and Today in Energy.",
